║ KALI LINUX VIRTUAL MACHINE - HELP ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SYSTEM COMMANDS:

whoami - Displays the current user

pwd - Displays the current working directory

cd [dir] - Changes the directory

ls [path] - Lists files and directories

clear - Clears the screen

exit - Exits the system

NETWORK COMMANDS:

ifconfig - Displays network interface information

ip - Advanced network configuration utility

ping [host] - Sends ICMP packets

traceroute [host] - Displays the route to a host

netstat - Displays network connections and open ports

ss - Socket statistics utility

route - Displays the routing table

whois [domain] - WHOIS information

dig [domain] - DNS lookup tool

nslookup [domain] - Name resolution query

SECURITY TOOLS:

nmap - Port scanning and service discovery

Metasploit - Penetration analysis framework

sqlmap - Automated SQL injection

Burp Suite - Web scanner

Hydra - Brute-force attack

hashcat - GPU password cracking

john - Hash cracking

aircrack-ng - WiFi cracking

Wireshark - Protocol analyzer

nikto - Web vulnerability scanner

gobuster - Directory enumeration

wpscan - WordPress scanner

lynis - Security auditing

FILE COMMANDS:

cat [file] - Displays file contents

echo [text] - Prints text

mkdir [dir] - Creates directory

touch [file] - Creates empty file

rm [file] - Deletes file

cp [src] [dst] - Copies file

mv [src] [dst] - Moves/renames file

grep [pattern] - Searches for pattern in files

find [path] - Searches for files

SYSTEM INFORMATION:

uname - Kernel information

hostname - Hostname

date - Current date and time

uptime - Uptime

df - Disk space

free - Available memory

ps - Running processes

top - Process monitor

UTILITIES:

tools - Lists all available tools

history - Displays command history

help - Displays this help

scan [type] - Performs a security scan

exploit [name] - Executes an exploit

payload [type] - Generates a payload
